Short:        Turn based dungeon crawler 'Hack and Slay'
Author:       Quantum Code Monk
Uploader:     quantumcodemonk@outlook.com
Type:         game/role
Version:      1.1
Architecture: m68k-amigaos
Distribution: aminet
Url:          https://quantumcodemonk.itch.io/



After playing "Hack and Slash" on a BBS sometime ago I felt the 
need to write my own version of that game. So I give you 
"Hack and Slay - stickman version" for the Amiga. :) 
It should run on almost any Amiga with a minimum resolution of 
640*400 running AmigaOS 2.0 or greater.

Main features of the game
- turn based
- 2 difficulty levels
- 4 playable characters classes
    - thief: can move quietly
    - knight: makes more damage
    - wizard: can cast spells
    - serf: can give first aid
- Auto-map
- 5 levels to explore
- Very small binary. Less than 100 kB
- Written in Blitz Basic

Minimum requirements
- 1 MB RAM
- 640*400 resolution 
- 68020 14MHz
- AmigaOS 2.0/3.x
- An Amiga (real or emulated)

Installation
Unpack the files to any location on your Amiga. Start by double clicking
on the programicon.

